1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,127
<i>What's happening?</i>

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:03,962
<i>I'm at the main entrance, boss.</i>

3
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:05,714
<i>It's getting chaotic here.</i>

4
00:00:05,797 --> 00:00:08,758
<i>A lot of people are going outside.</i>
<i>Police officers are coming in.</i>

5
00:00:08,842 --> 00:00:10,552
[OFFICER] <i>Hey!</i>

6
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,220
<i>The police are aware of us now.</i>

7
00:00:12,303 --> 00:00:14,097
<i>- Conrad, Roman.</i>
<i>- Boss.</i>

8
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:16,683
[EMIL] <i>Get to the senator's son.</i>

9
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:18,643
<i>Senator Maristella.</i>

10
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:21,730
<i>Sir Emil is sending you</i>
<i>a cordial invitation.</i>

11
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:23,815
[SCREAMS]

12
00:00:23,898 --> 00:00:24,774
- [GRETA]<i> Liam!</i>
<i>- Ma!</i>

13
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:26,818
<i>- We need to go.</i>
<i>- I was looking for you. Why?</i>

14
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:28,778
<i>Emil Padua and his men are alive.</i>

15
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:30,363
<i>They're here at the hospital.</i>

16
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:31,781
[LUCAS] <i>Boss Emil.</i>

17
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:34,451
<i>I have Liam and Greta Roja with me.</i>

18
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,036
<i>Take them up.</i>

19
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:40,123
[ALL THREE GRUNTING]

20
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:41,916
<i>Stay back!</i>

21
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:45,128
[SHOUTS]

22
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:48,798
- [OLSEN YELLS]
- [EXPLOSION BOOMS]

23
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:52,218
<i>Her temperature's still high.</i>
<i>Her fever could've relapsed.</i>

24
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:53,386
<i>I'm not a real nurse!</i>

25
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:56,014
<i>I know. That's why we</i>
<i>need to find a doctor.</i>

26
00:00:56,097 --> 00:00:58,391
[GWEN] <i>Doc! Doc, wait.</i>

27
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:02,353
<i>Everyone already evacuated.</i>
<i>Can you help my friend?</i>

28
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:06,983
<i>- They have Greta and Liam!</i>
<i>- Who are they?</i>

29
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,069
<i>I think it's</i>

30
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:10,278
<i>Emil Padua?</i>

31
00:01:10,361 --> 00:01:12,614
<i>Olsen? Where is he?</i>

32
00:01:12,697 --> 00:01:14,282
[LIAM] <i>Hey! Dude! Wake up!</i>

33
00:01:14,365 --> 00:01:16,785
<i>- Let's go. There's nothing we can do.</i>
- [LIAM] <i>I won't leave him!</i>

34
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:20,246
<i>You told me yourself, remember?</i>
<i>That Olsen might be my brother?</i>

35
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:23,208
<i>Dude, come on. Let's go.</i>

36
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,210
<i>No one's leaving.</i>

37
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:26,920
[EMIL] <i>Get up!</i>

38
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:29,297
- [GRUNTS SOFTLY]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

39
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:30,965
<i>Move!</i>

40
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:39,432
- [SIREN WAILING]
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:40,850
[MAN] Hurry! Come on!

42
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:46,940
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

43
00:01:48,691 --> 00:01:55,365
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

44
00:01:55,448 --> 00:02:01,913
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:13,174
[LIAM, OLSEN GRUNTING]

46
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:19,764
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

47
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:27,397
[FREDO] Boss! Welcome to heaven!

48
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:30,984
[WHIMPERS]

49
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:35,613
- [GRUNTING HEAVILY]
- [DADO] Move it.

50
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:37,991
[GRETA WHIMPERS]

51
00:02:38,074 --> 00:02:42,620
- [LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY]
- [DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,122
[OLSEN BREATHING HEAVILY]

53
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:45,623
- [LIAM] Olsen.
- [GRETA GRUNTS]

54
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:52,714
- [DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

55
00:02:54,674 --> 00:02:56,342
[OLSEN WHIMPERS]

56
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:00,138
Get inside.

57
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:14,777
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:46,601
[DADO] Get inside.

59
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:49,354
[OLSEN COUGHS IN THE DISTANCE]

60
00:03:49,437 --> 00:03:51,981
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:56,361
[OLSEN COUGHING]

62
00:03:56,444 --> 00:03:57,320
[EMIL] Hurry up!

63
00:03:57,403 --> 00:04:02,867
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

64
00:04:04,118 --> 00:04:05,995
[LABORED BREATHING]

65
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:08,248
- Bro, are you okay?
- Stay over there!

66
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:09,207
[GRETA YELPS]

67
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,751
[OLSEN COUGHING]

68
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:17,006
Olsen!

69
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:20,260
Olsen.

70
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:21,844
Olsen!

71
00:04:23,846 --> 00:04:24,931
Olsen?

72
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,099
Olsen!

73
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,270
Olsen.

74
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,230
Olsen.

75
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:33,773
[SCREAMS]

76
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:35,275
Wendy! Wendy!

77
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:37,652
Leave, Wendy.

78
00:04:37,735 --> 00:04:39,320
Get out of the hospital.

79
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:41,864
- Come on, let's go.
- I can't!

80
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:44,284
I can't leave Olsen.

81
00:04:44,993 --> 00:04:46,744
He's all I have.

82
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:51,124
Why won't they just die already?

83
00:04:51,207 --> 00:04:52,292
Why?

84
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:53,418
Why?!

85
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:58,298
Well, if Emil Padua's men are alive,
that means…

86
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:01,634
Emil is still alive. He's here.

87
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,845
He's here for his daughter.

88
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:05,596
And for me.

89
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,181
You?

90
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:10,560
Why you?

91
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:16,649
- [EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [ELECTRICITY BUZZING]

92
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,110
Wendy, Emil has a huge grudge against me.

93
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,196
I'm really his target.

94
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,282
He wants revenge

95
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:26,909
because I had an affair with his daughter.

96
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:31,205
And now she's missing, and Emil thinks
I know where she is, but I don't.

97
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:32,332
I don't know.

98
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,666
Please…

99
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,045
[MAGNUS] <i>You all must go now.</i>

100
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:39,088
<i>Come on.</i>

101
00:05:39,172 --> 00:05:40,631
<i>You're not coming?</i>

102
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:44,594
<i>I will do everything I can</i>
<i>to save all of you</i>

103
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:47,138
<i>because you're my responsibility.</i>

104
00:05:47,221 --> 00:05:48,973
<i>You're going to stay here?</i>

105
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:50,433
<i>I have to do this, Wendy.</i>

106
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:53,436
Now I know.

107
00:05:54,812 --> 00:05:58,566
I finally know why you wanted
to face them alone.

108
00:05:59,442 --> 00:06:01,027
Is it because I feel like…

109
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:02,695
[NO AUDIBLE DIALOG]

110
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,947
<i>…everything that happened</i>
<i>at La Playa Roja,</i>

111
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:06,657
<i>everything happening to us…</i>

112
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:10,369
is my fault, Wendy.

113
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:15,124
My father died because of you!

114
00:06:16,417 --> 00:06:20,505
If anything happens to Olsen,
it will be because of you?!

115
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:24,050
I won't abandon Olsen, Wendy.

116
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:26,511
I treat him like my son.

117
00:06:26,594 --> 00:06:27,804
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

118
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,389
Not knowing it's possible that he's…

119
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:31,682
He's what?

120
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,686
Olsen is like a son to me.

121
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:38,523
There's a possibility that he is my son.

122
00:06:38,606 --> 00:06:40,858
- Right, Wendy?
- Huh?

123
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:43,778
That's what Greta thinks, Wendy.

124
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:45,029
No!

125
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:46,614
- Olsen is my son!
- No!

126
00:06:46,697 --> 00:06:49,867
Wendy! Wendy, please be honest with me.

127
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:51,786
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:06:51,869 --> 00:06:54,789
Something happened between us
24 years ago.

129
00:06:54,872 --> 00:06:57,375
You disappeared all of a sudden,

130
00:06:57,458 --> 00:07:00,002
and then you came back with a son.

131
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:03,422
Olsen is not your son.

132
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:05,258
You're not his father.

133
00:07:05,341 --> 00:07:09,220
Just because Greta had that thought,
you think it's all true?

134
00:07:09,303 --> 00:07:11,305
Then who is his father?

135
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:12,598
Who is Olsen's father?

136
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:16,853
Magnus, I met someone after we broke up.

137
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:19,397
Greta knew that.

138
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:23,609
He was a bodyguard of one of
the resort's regular guests.

139
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,488
You thought wrong.

140
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,699
You and Greta are wrong.

141
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:32,076
Olsen is not your son.

142
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:33,995
Fine.

143
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:35,621
Fine, it doesn't matter.

144
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:39,250
I'm still willing to risk
my life for Olsen.

145
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:43,463
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

146
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:46,757
[MAGNUS GRUNTS]

147
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:51,804
We will find our sons, okay?

148
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:55,892
[HOPEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

149
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:05,860
Teach me how to use this.

150
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:11,866
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:22,460
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SIREN WAILING]

152
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:26,506
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

153
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:30,259
- Sir.
- What's happening here?

154
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:31,886
- [OFFICER 1] Sir.
- [CABRAL] Move! Hurry!

155
00:08:31,969 --> 00:08:33,346
[CABRAL] Secure all patients!

156
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:35,306
Prioritize the safety
of everyone here, okay?

157
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:36,390
[OFFICER 2] Yes, sir.

158
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:37,558
Any development?

159
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:40,353
We have identified the location
of the hostage takers.

160
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:41,354
They're in that building.

161
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:43,439
[OFFICER 3] Move! Move!

162
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,608
- Have you set up already?
- Yes, sir.

163
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:52,240
<i>Evacuation is still ongoing</i>
<i>here at the hostage crisis</i>

164
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,991
<i>at St. John's Hospital.</i>

165
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:57,286
<i>Three of the suspects were</i>
<i>identified as Emilio Padua,</i>

166
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,580
<i>Diosdado Menor, and Lucas Sebastian,</i>

167
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:02,833
<i>who were reported dead</i>
<i>during the La Playa siege,</i>

168
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:05,836
<i>but are now confirmed to be alive.</i>

169
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,673
<i>As of now,</i>
<i>authorities are still confirming</i>

170
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:11,968
<i>the number of hostage takers</i>
<i>and the hostages they're holding.</i>

171
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:13,761
<i>But according to the cop we interviewed,</i>

172
00:09:13,844 --> 00:09:16,556
<i>there are still civilians, patients,</i>
<i>and medical staff</i>

173
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:19,225
<i>who are trapped in St. John's Hospital.</i>

174
00:09:19,308 --> 00:09:22,478
<i>And based on the leaked video</i>
<i>from the hostage takers,</i>

175
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:25,022
<i>they took as hostages</i>
<i>Senator Eduardo Maristella,</i>

176
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,275
<i>his son, Macky Maristella,</i>

177
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:30,278
<i>Greta Roja, the wife</i>
<i>of the owner of La Playa Roja,</i>

178
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:32,738
<i>and their son, Liam Roja.</i>

179
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:35,575
<i>This is Sam Gabrino, reporting.</i>

180
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:40,204
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,711
- [OLSEN COUGHS]
- Go.

182
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:49,005
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

183
00:09:50,214 --> 00:09:51,465
[OLSEN GROANS]

184
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:56,137
[DADO] Don't try to remove that.

185
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:59,348
I'm the only one who can remove it.

186
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:02,727
It's not like the one I put on you before.

187
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:06,564
You can't outsmart me this time.

188
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:14,864
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:19,118
[BOMB TICKING]

190
00:10:19,201 --> 00:10:20,244
<i>Run!</i>

191
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:26,208
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

192
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:43,726
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:47,480
[DADO] Fifty meters.

194
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:50,024
It has a limit of 50 meters.

195
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,609
Don't try to go beyond that,

196
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:54,987
because if you get more than 50 meters
away, this is what will happen to you.

197
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,072
Watch this.

198
00:10:58,282 --> 00:11:04,372
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

199
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:14,006
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:36,612
[BEEPING]

201
00:11:36,695 --> 00:11:40,408
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:43,035
- [EXPLOSION BOOMS]
- [POLICE GASP]

203
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:43,994
[OLSEN COUGHS]

204
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,664
- [WENDY GASPS]
- [EXPLOSION ECHOES]

205
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:48,457
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

206
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,708
Wendy!

207
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:52,920
- Call the bomb squad.
- [OFFICER] Okay.

208
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:58,467
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:00,469
Come on.

210
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:08,394
[OLSEN GROANS, COUGHS]

211
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:12,773
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:14,233
[OLSEN GROANS]

213
00:12:14,316 --> 00:12:15,401
[LUCAS CHUCKLES]

214
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:23,659
The bombs will detonate automatically.

215
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,704
If you don't want to explode,

216
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:29,415
then don't try to escape.

217
00:12:29,498 --> 00:12:32,710
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:34,587
Your father will save us.

219
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:41,844
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:48,893
[POLICE OFFICER 1] Sir, they're in.

221
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:54,273
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:13,834
[LIGHTS FLICKERING]

223
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:19,465
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:36,649
[MUSIC BECOMES SINISTER]

225
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:40,694
- Head to the exit! Move!
- [PEOPLE CLAMORING]

226
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:42,363
Hurry up, keep running!

227
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:44,615
Move! Go, go, go!

228
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:47,326
- Move, move!
- [WOMAN CRYING]

229
00:13:47,409 --> 00:13:48,786
Keep moving!

230
00:13:48,869 --> 00:13:54,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:13:56,752 --> 00:13:59,213
- Move, move, move! Hurry!
- Move! Quickly, quickly!

232
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,131
Move!

233
00:14:02,841 --> 00:14:05,135
[LIGHT FOOTSTEPS]

234
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:06,220
[WENDY PANTING]

235
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:07,721
[SOFTLY] Up there.

236
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:13,519
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

237
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:16,564
It's clear. Let's go.

238
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:34,290
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,296
[BOMBS TICKING]

240
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:42,590
Do you think you can
get away with this again?

241
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:49,054
The police will find out soon
that we have VIP hostages.

242
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:50,806
So my answer is yes.

243
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:53,601
We will get away with this.

244
00:14:53,684 --> 00:15:00,524
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

245
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:16,290
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

246
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:17,708
Senator.

247
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:28,510
Olsen!

248
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:33,432
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:15:33,515 --> 00:15:35,351
[LINE RINGING]

250
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:37,603
Is this the Alicante Police Station?

251
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:44,944
Who is in charge of the hostage situation
at St. John's Hospital?

252
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:48,989
I need to send something to them.

253
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:55,996
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

254
00:15:57,706 --> 00:15:59,083
- Radio.
- [POLICE OFFICER 2] Sir.

255
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,168
[RADIO STATIC CRACKLES]

256
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:03,796
All units inside the hospital.

257
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:06,131
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

258
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:07,257
Abort mission.

259
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,094
Withdraw and exit
the hospital immediately.

260
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,387
Yes, sir.

261
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:12,596
[RADIO STATIC CRACKLES]

262
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,682
- Move out!
- Move!

263
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:16,183
We're being pulled out.

264
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:17,810
[RADIO STATIC CRACKLES]

265
00:16:20,896 --> 00:16:27,194
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

266
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:49,675
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:10,320
Have your colleagues gotten out?
No one should remain inside.

268
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:11,905
Two are reportedly still inside, sir.

269
00:17:11,989 --> 00:17:13,741
The ones assigned to Captain Jacinto.

270
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:15,492
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

271
00:17:15,576 --> 00:17:18,037
[REPORTER 1] Sir, sir!
Why did you pull out the SWAT team?

272
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:20,748
[REPORTER 2] Sir, what's the next move
for the police force?

273
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:26,754
- [MACHINE BEEPING]
- [HANDCUFFS RATTLE]

274
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:27,880
[SIGHS]

275
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:32,926
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

276
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,137
- [RADIO STATIC CRACKLES]
- [LOUD RATTLING]

277
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:37,056
Yes, sir. We're still at our post.

278
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:41,894
Okay. But we will pull out
along with the patient.

279
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:43,687
- What happened?
- [DOOR OPENS]

280
00:17:43,771 --> 00:17:46,190
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:17:46,273 --> 00:17:47,274
Come on.

282
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:48,942
Hey!

283
00:17:50,903 --> 00:17:51,904
[GROANS]

284
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:54,782
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

285
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:01,205
Boss! Boss!

286
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:04,124
[BOMBS TICKING]

287
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:06,085
Release us,

288
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:08,128
and I'll give you anything you want.

289
00:18:08,212 --> 00:18:09,129
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

290
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:11,840
I will find a way to get you
out of this mess.

291
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:13,342
Away from prison.

292
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:17,596
It's not that simple, Senator.

293
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:21,100
What else do you want? Money?

294
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:24,603
I can get it for you.

295
00:18:24,686 --> 00:18:26,480
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:27,648
All right.

297
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:31,860
Since we're talking about money,

298
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:34,446
that's my priority for now.

299
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:35,989
Conrad, Roman.

300
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:37,032
Boss.

301
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,827
Bring Captain Jacinto to me.

302
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,246
We have something to discuss.

303
00:18:42,329 --> 00:18:47,709
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

304
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:51,797
Also, if you find stragglers
anywhere in the hospital,

305
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:54,842
bring them up here.

306
00:18:55,425 --> 00:18:59,304
We need more hostages.

307
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:00,472
Don't worry.

308
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,516
It's safe downstairs.
The cops were pulled out.

309
00:19:02,599 --> 00:19:05,978
That was the agreement I made
with the general.

310
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:07,729
- Copy, boss.
- Go on.

311
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:13,819
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

312
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:31,628
<i>- We need to clean your wound.</i>
- [JOY YELPS]

313
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:35,674
- [MADDIE] <i>Mommy…</i>
<i>- Don't look. Don't.</i>

314
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:37,134
<i>Faster, faster.</i>

315
00:19:37,217 --> 00:19:39,011
[MINNIE] <i>Where do we go now?</i>

316
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:41,096
[DADO] <i>The building is secured.</i>

317
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,182
<i>This is a bullet wound.</i>
<i>How did she get this?</i>

318
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,142
<i>Just treat her.</i>

319
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,936
[WHIMPERS] <i>I'm just looking for my son.</i>

320
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:49,271
<i>Stay right there!</i>

321
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:50,397
- [WENDY YELPS]
- [GUNSHOT]

322
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,399
<i>You'll pay for everything you've done!</i>

323
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:55,235
<i>Good for you.</i>
<i>Your family is all together.</i>

324
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:56,737
[MAGNUS] <i>Leave them out of this!</i>

325
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:58,197
<i>I'm the one you want, right?</i>

326
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,532
<i>Let's settle this once and for all!</i>
<i>Just the two of us!</i>

327
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:03,744
<i>The building has been almost evacuated.</i>

328
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:06,288
<i>"Almost"? They aren't sure?</i>

329
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:07,915
<i>The hospital security team can't verify</i>

330
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:10,250
<i>if there are any more civilians</i>
<i>left inside, sir.</i>

331
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,211
[MILA] <i>Get out of there.</i>

332
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:15,672
<i>If you want me to get out of here alive,</i>
<i>you'll help us.</i>

333
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,758
<i>Lucas, I can't do this anymore.</i>

334
00:20:17,841 --> 00:20:21,595
[LUCAS] <i>You can do this.</i>
<i>We can do this.</i>

335
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:27,559
<i>We need to make this sacrifice</i>
<i>to give our child a better life.</i>

336
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:32,064
<i>Liam.</i>

337
00:20:32,147 --> 00:20:35,025
<i>Why did you say earlier</i>
<i>that we might be brothers?</i>

338
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:38,946
<i>Isn't it better if we all know the truth?</i>

339
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:40,197
<i>What truth?</i>

340
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,490
<i>Greta.</i>

341
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:45,452
<i>Whatever you're thinking, it isn't true.</i>

342
00:20:45,535 --> 00:20:46,578
<i>Ma, come on.</i>

343
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:51,667
<i>Why would Ma'am Greta think that?</i>

344
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:54,378
[OLSEN] <i>Huh?</i>

345
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:58,257
<i>Because your mother and my husband</i>
<i>had an affair.</i>

346
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:04,221
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
